    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9800 - ADJUSTMENTS - CAB FRONT AND REAR MOUNT
        ADJUSTMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1601822" svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CAB FRONT AND REAR MOUNT ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen mounting bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601893">Item 2, Figure 93</hotlnk>) at right front lower hinge bracket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601893">Item 3, Figure 93</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1601893" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1601893" filename="../figg16/g1601893.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 93. Cylinder Assembly and Lower Hinge Bracket</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. CYLINDER ASSEMBLY AND SAFETY STOP</callout1>
                <callout1>2. MOUNTING BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>3. LOWER HINGE BRACKET</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>- Do not remove mounting bolts or damage to the cab can result during adjusting procedure.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Raise cab and engage cylinder safety stop (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601893">Item 1, Figure 93</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen mounting bolts at both rear latch pad brackets (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601894">Figure 94</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1601894" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic id="g1601894" filename="../figg16/g1601894.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                     scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 94. Rear Latch Pad Brackets</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">At left latch pad bracket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601894">Figure 94</hotlnk>), loosen mounting bolts and set distance between centerline
                of left latch pad bolt and vertical side of left frame rail to 6.75 inches (171 mm).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disengage cylinder safety stop (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601893">Item 1, Figure 93</hotlnk>), lower cab and check cab alignment with chassis.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten left latch pad bracket mounting bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601894">Figure 94</hotlnk>) to 23 to 27 ft-lbs. (31 to 37 Nm) and right front lower
                hinge bracket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601893">Item 3, Figure 93</hotlnk>) mounting bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601893">Item 2, Figure 93</hotlnk>) to 110 to 120 ft-lbs. (149 to 163 Nm).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Raise and lower cab and check cab alignment again.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make adjustment as required to square cab with chassis.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Adjust right rear latch pad bracket so that latch and pad "Vs" are in line to line contact
                on both sides (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601894">Figure 94</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten right rear latch pad bracket mounting bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601894">Figure 94</hotlnk>) to 23 to 27 ft-lbs. (31 to 37 Nm).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
